overview: The user initiated the conversation by requesting a thorough aesthetic
  review and improvement for their sleep questionnaire app, which they felt was
  visually lacking. I began by analyzing the existing design, identifying areas
  for improvement in color, typography, layout, and form elements. The initial
  phase involved implementing a new sleep-themed color palette, redesigning the
  main form layout with decorative elements and an improved progress indicator,
  and enhancing the welcome screen with feature cards. I also polished core UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders, and applied the new
  card-style grouping to the . Subsequently, a console error
  regarding  input values was identified and fixed by modifying the
   component to safely handle such values. The final phase focused on
  applying the consistent sleep-themed styling to all remaining questionnaire
  sections and creating custom utility classes for alerts to ensure visual
  cohesion across the entire application. This iterative approach transformed
  the app from a generic template look to a professional, calming, and visually
  appealing sleep health assessment tool.
